On Wed, Nov 19, 2014 at 03:51:26PM -0500, Kevin Cozens wrote:
> The description on the website does indicate it is 24". If it said
> 27" before they have corrected the listing.

It clearly said 2560x1440 Dell U2713HM.

And looking at the URL:
http://www.walmart.ca/en/ip/dell-27-2560-x-1440-led-ips-monitor/6000189477880

Seems pretty clear that it is a Dell, 27", 2560x1440, LED backlight,
IPS panel, monitor.  Not sure how else one could read that.

And the current description says:

  2560x1440 WQHD resolution: Over 3.6 million pixels provide amazing
  clarity on a spacious 27" LED-backlit display.
  Accurate color right out of the box: Carefully color calibrated at
  the factory, the U2713HM monitor features more than 99-percent sRGB
  color space for impressive color from the moment you set it up.

And then the right side says 24", which contradicts the main description.

So the resolution does not exist in a 24" that is listed, the model
listed is a 27", they just changed 27 to 24 in a few places, but it is
still all wrong.

> If you ordered one, kept it, and have put it in to use, what are
> your impressions of it?

